quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,172,"And [mention] when your Lord took from the children of Adam - from their loins - their descendants and made them testify of themselves, [saying to them], "
  7,173,"Or [lest] you say, "
  7,174,"And thus do We [explain in] detail the verses, and perhaps they will return.{1}",footnotes:1:To the way of Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā), from their diversions and deviations.
  9,76,"But when He gave them from His bounty, they were stingy with it and turned away while they refused."
  9,77,"So He penalized them with hypocrisy in their hearts until the Day they will meet Him - because they failed Allāh in what they promised Him and because they [habitually] used to lie."
  9,78,"Did they not know that Allāh knows their secrets and their private conversations and that Allāh is the Knower of the unseen?"
  10,34,"Say, "
  10,35,"Say, "
  10,36,"And most of them follow not except assumption. Indeed, assumption avails not against the truth at all. Indeed, Allāh is Knowing of what they do."
  11,1,"Alif, Lām, Rā.{1} [This is] a Book whose verses are perfected and then presented in detail from [one who is] Wise and Aware{2}",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:1.],footnotes:2:[Refer to footnotes of 6:18.]
  11,2,"[Through a messenger, saying], "
  11,3,"And [saying], "
